# Arc Reactor Subsystem

The Arc Reactor subsystem serves as the central power and data nerve center of the ROS-IM suit.

![Arc Reactor Subsystem](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Abhi13-coder/Ros-IM/main/1764154345537.jpg)

---

## Integration Overview

- **High-performance CPU**
  - 64-bit
  - 16-core
- **Modular RAM Clusters**
  - Including Mega-RAM and RAM managers
- **Distributed Battery & Energy Management**
- **Wireless Communication Subsystems**

---

## System Components

### CPU & RAM Cluster

- **Processor:**  
  64-bit / 16-core processor  
  Manages overall computation and real-time decision-making.
- **RAM Banks & Managers:**  
  Communicate with distributed microcontroller nodes:
  - Arduino
  - ESP32
  - Raspberry Pi
- **Mega-RAM:**  
  32GB for advanced AI workloads & rapid sensor fusion.

---

### Battery Architecture

- Multiple battery units (“battery ultra”) supply power redundantly across all subsystems.
- Batteries are monitored and balanced for safety and longevity.

---

### Wireless Communication

- Integrated chip transmitters:
  - WiFi
  - Bluetooth
- Functions:
  - Remote control
  - Diagnostics
  - Data relay

---

### Microcontroller Integration

- Node connections (via RAM managers & ROS2 processors) to:
  - ESP32
  - Arduino Uno
  - Raspberry Pi (AI, RAM)
- Each microcontroller:
  - Dedicated storage
  - Battery support
- RAM managers ensure:
  - Efficient memory allocation
  - System synchronization
  - Modular expansion

---

### Storage & Data Management

- Onboard storage modules for high-speed data logging and retrieval.

---

## ROS Integration

### ROS2 Nodes

- Each RAM manager & microcontroller subsystem operates as a dedicated ROS2 node,
- All communication over well-defined ROS topics and services.
- Central CPU acts as ROS master node, coordinating distributed tasks & real-time updates.

---

## Diagnostics & Safety

- Battery levels
- Memory usage
- Communication integrity
- All monitored & published via ROS topics for:
  - Live diagnostics
  - Emergency fallback

---

## Significance

The Arc Reactor module is the foundational layer of the ROS-IM suit, enabling all future modules to interface efficiently with centralized power, computation, and connectivity.

Its modular architecture supports:
- Robust upgrades
- Distributed intelligence
- Advanced safety protocols essential for wearable robotics.